==English==
===Etymology===
From French [[symbolique]] or Latin [[symbolicus]], from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[συμβολικός]]''' (''symbolikos'') "of or belonging to a [[symbol]]".

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒlɪk|-ɒlɪk]]

===Adjective===

'''symbolic'''
# Pertaining to a [[symbol]].
# Referring to something with an [[implicit]] meaning.

